# PowerShell scripts require UTF-8 BOM for Windows PowerShell 5.1 compatibility.
#
# Without BOM, PS 5.1 reads .ps1 files as Windows-1252 (system default).
# Non-ASCII characters (em dashes, etc.) get mangled: UTF-8 byte 0x94
# maps to U+201D (right double quote) in Windows-1252, and PowerShell
# treats smart quotes as string delimiters â€” causing silent parse failures
# with misleading error messages.
#
# NOTE: git's working-tree-encoding=UTF-8-BOM requires iconv support for
# that encoding name, which NixOS's glibc does not provide. Instead, the
# BOM is committed directly and enforced by a nix flake check
# (lint-ps1-encoding) that validates BOM presence on all .ps1 files.
*.ps1 text
